PLACEHOLDER - READ THIS CAREFULLY
==================================

This file (google-services.json) is a PLACEHOLDER.
You MUST replace it with your real google-services.json from Firebase.

HOW TO GET YOUR REAL FILE:
1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Open your project
3. Click the gear icon → "Project settings"
4. Scroll down to "Your apps"
5. Click your Android app (com.yapapa.app)
6. Click "Download google-services.json"
7. DELETE this placeholder file
8. PUT your downloaded google-services.json in this exact folder:
   android/app/google-services.json

IMPORTANT: The real file looks like this (just an example, yours will have real values):
{
  "project_info": {
    "project_number": "123456789",
    "project_id": "yapapa-xxxxx",
    "storage_bucket": "yapapa-xxxxx.appspot.com"
  },
  "client": [
    {
      "client_info": {
        "mobilesdk_app_id": "1:123456789:android:abcdefgh",
        "android_client_info": {
          "package_name": "com.yapapa.app"
        }
      },
      ...
    }
  ]
}

The GitHub Actions build.yml will automatically inject your real
google-services.json via the GOOGLE_SERVICES_JSON secret you set in GitHub.
So you only need to manually replace this file if building locally.

DO NOT commit your real google-services.json to GitHub.
The secret approach in build.yml handles this safely.
